Setting out her vision for the future of Britain, the Trade Minster took a swipe at the smear tactics being deployed by her rivals. Speaking at the Conservative Home hustings, Ms Mordaunt said: "I don't want mudslinging, I want all of us candidates and our colleagues to show the nation that we're building a team together." She repeated her previous remarks that she was determined to run a "positive campaign". FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...